From 71d24ce65a8b78bc44fc03e5487d2bae96bc679f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aaron Paterson <apaterson@pm.me>
Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 21:49:40 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] odb: add helper backend for external object storage

Introduce `ODB_STORAGE_FORMAT_HELPER`, a new object storage backend
that delegates object operations to an external process. This follows
the same pattern as transport helpers (git-remote-*) and credential
helpers (git-credential-*).

The helper binary is discovered as "git-odb-<name>" in PATH. It is
invoked with the object directory path as its sole argument and
communicates via a line-based protocol on stdin/stdout:

  capabilities -> list supported commands
  info <oid>   -> type size (or "missing")
  get <oid>    -> type size + raw data (or "missing")
  put <oid> <type> <size> + raw data -> oid
  have <oid>   -> true/false
  list         -> oid type size per line, blank line terminates

Configuration uses the URI format already established for ref storage:

  [extensions]
    objectStorage = helper://sqlite

This sets odb_storage_format to ODB_STORAGE_FORMAT_HELPER with
"sqlite" as the payload, causing git to spawn "git-odb-sqlite" and
pass all object operations through it.

The ODB storage format and payload are now set on the repository
struct before calling setup_git_env(), so that odb_source_new() can
select the correct backend when creating the object database.

Include unit tests for the helper format lookup and an integration
test (t0620) that exercises the full write/read round-trip through
a shell-based test helper.

Signed-off-by: Aaron Willoughby <aaron@omniband.org>
